Package: fastmlm
Title: Fast Estimation of Multilevel Linear Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ross A.", "Dunne", email = "sadneurons@pm.me",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits linear and generalised linear mixed-effects models 4-14x
    faster than 'lme4' using a high-performance C++ backend. Supports LMMs via
    fmlm() and GLMMs (binomial, Poisson, Gamma) via fglmm(). Features include
    a custom formula parser, formula/data caching for repeated fits (bootstrap,
    simulation), a C++ L-BFGS-B optimiser, CHOLMOD supernodal sparse Cholesky
    factorisation (via 'Matrix'), precomputed sparse matrix mappings, optional
    CUDA GPU acceleration, Satterthwaite degrees of freedom (with exact mode
    matching 'lmerTest'), restricted cubic splines via 'rms', and integration
    with 'emmeans' and 'broom.mixed'. Provides a drop-in interface using the
    same formula syntax as lmer() and glmer() from 'lme4'.
